Project: High Speed Database (HSD)

Description:
Intel uses HSD as a Bug Tracking system for its projects over processors and chipsets. HSD provides a customized and project specific solution to each project. There are around 600 projects in Intel which are using HSD for bug tracking. HSD consists of a frame work, which is a combination of HSD .NET components and Data Base Engine. HSD .NET components provide the custom controls, base classes for architecture support and data base handling. Database engine consists of the data base logic and structure which is common to all the HSD projects. Project which uses HSD for bug tracking will be provided with a unique data base and user interface. Each platform of a project is called as Focus. HSD customized project can contain different focus like bug, da_help, dacct, ccb, and eco. Most of the business logic and validations are implemented in data base. Projects are categorized into different groups and there will be an inter relation between projects. Records can be rolled up/down among the projects, and can be pushed, cloned with in the project and different foci. SLA can be implemented on a focus, to track the time required for fixing a bug or enhancement. Each record in a focus will have different states defined in state machine which indicates the status of Bug. Admin tool is common to all the projects which is used by admin's to set the project level settings and to maintain lookup values, users, roles, logical groups and field values.

