Client                 : Consolidated Graphics, TX                               Jan 12 - August 12
Role                           : Developer
Project: TSSG Gateway

Description:
Consolidated Graphics is the world's leading provider of high-end digital printing solutions. Ordering systems in CGX depends on external shipping provider. I worked on integrating the ordering systems with shipping provider ADSI. We have developed a gateway layer which will act as a broker service between CGX ordering systems and ADSI. Gateway is developed as a WCF service. We have integrated Storefront, classic, Promail and streamline ordering systems with Gateway. Using Gateway ADSI can get the Shipping details of order from corresponding ordering system and can update shipping information for a particular order. It receives, validate, Authenticate, analyze cXML request and identify targeted ordering system using Routing Manager. Translation layer translate cXML request to XML using XSLT and sends it to requested ordering system's web service. Ordering systems are having Web services to communicate. Web service process the request and sends response back to Gateway in XML format. Translation layer again translate this XML to cXML and then send response to sender.  We have developed Web services for Promail, Streamline and utilized the existing Web services of Storefront and Classic.


